# Compass Agent — deployment config
# Copy to .env and fill in your values (never commit .env).
#
# Compass has no external API credentials of its own — it routes to other
# agents. All runtime/model/registry defaults inherit from
# config/constellation.yaml. Only put deployment-specific overrides here.

# ----- OPTIONAL: service binding -----
# HOST=0.0.0.0
# PORT=8000

# ----- OPTIONAL: pinned agent state directory -----
# When set, ``scripts/run_local.py`` writes per-agent state (task_store,
# checkpoints, session data) under ``$ARTIFACT_ROOT/.agent-state/<agent>``
# instead of the project-relative ``data/agent-state/`` default.
#
# IMPORTANT: if you set this here, use an absolute path that exists on
# every machine and every user account that runs the agent. A path tied
# to a specific user account (e.g. ``/Users/alice/...``) will silently
# fail to launch with ``PermissionError`` for any other user, and a path
# under a non-existent parent will fail with ``FileNotFoundError``.
# Either leave this commented out (recommended for local development) or
# point it at a shared directory that all operators can write to.
# ARTIFACT_ROOT=/var/lib/constellation/artifacts
